<DOC><DOCNO> AP890622-0294 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-22-89 1059EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-HCA-SaleAgreement     06-22 0165</FIRST><SECOND>BC-HCA-Sale Agreement,0172</SECOND><HEAD>Hospital Corp., British Company Reach Tentative Sale Agreement</HEAD><DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hospital Corp. of America has tentativelyagreed to sell 10 hospitals and seven nursing homes in the UnitedKingdom to a British health care group, HCA officials announcedThursday.   The $142 million sale to BUPA Health Services Ltd. must beapproved by HCA's board of directors. The two reached an agreementin principle but have no definitive purchase agreement, theNashville health care giant said in a news release.   The sale is expected to be finalized within 45 days.   ``There can be no assurance that the conditions will be satisfiedand that the transaction will be consummated,'' the writtenstatement said.   The facilities are owned by a British HCA subsidiary called HCAUnited Kingdom Ltd. BUPA Health Services is a subsidiary of BritishUnited Provident Association Ltd.   Hospital Corp. is a wholly-owned subsidiary of HCA-Hospital Corp.of America, formed in the recently completed, management-ledleveraged buyout of the company.</TEXT></DOC>